2010-05-27  Sebastian Pipping <sping@gentoo.org>

	* Build system: fix make distcheck (bug #22)

2010-05-26  Jan Hauke Rahm <jhr@debian.org>

	* 0.2: the still-not-ready-but-now-with-great-features release
	* post-dot digit precision: For e.g. enum 0.1 .. 0.4 automatically
	  detect a step of 0.1 instead of 1
	* Formatting: enum now supports several options to change the output
	  format using getopt_long, e.g. --precision, --format etc. which is
	  supposed to be very jot like
	* Random: enum can output the calculated values in a pseudo-random way
	* man page: give it some real content

